WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.670
Good news:

00:00:01.670 --> 00:00:03.681
no terminal needed for this one!

00:00:03.681 --> 00:00:06.362
We'll open a full VS Code right in

00:00:06.362 --> 00:00:07.032
the browser,

00:00:07.032 --> 00:00:08.037
create some files,

00:00:08.037 --> 00:00:09.378
run a few commands,

00:00:09.378 --> 00:00:12.059
and watch the kernel keep it all inside

00:00:12.059 --> 00:00:12.729
the repo.

00:00:13.503 --> 00:00:14.647
Here's the idea.

00:00:14.647 --> 00:00:17.317
The editor doesn't run on your laptop.

00:00:17.317 --> 00:00:19.987
It runs inside the repo's sandbox on

00:00:19.987 --> 00:00:20.749
the server,

00:00:20.749 --> 00:00:23.419
and your browser reaches it through an

00:00:23.419 --> 00:00:24.182
SSH tunnel.

00:00:24.182 --> 00:00:25.707
So the file tree,

00:00:25.707 --> 00:00:26.852
the built-in terminal,

00:00:26.852 --> 00:00:29.521
and anything you launch from it see

00:00:29.521 --> 00:00:31.428
exactly what the repo sees,

00:00:31.428 --> 00:00:32.572
and nothing else.

00:00:35.843 --> 00:00:36.613
One command.

00:00:36.613 --> 00:00:39.309
The CLI installs the editor server on

00:00:39.309 --> 00:00:40.464
the machine once,

00:00:40.464 --> 00:00:42.775
starts it inside the repo sandbox,

00:00:42.775 --> 00:00:43.931
opens a tunnel,

00:00:43.931 --> 00:00:45.856
and hands you a link.

00:00:45.856 --> 00:00:47.397
No local VS Code,

00:00:47.397 --> 00:00:49.322
no extensions to set up.

00:00:52.322 --> 00:00:54.134
That URL is your editor.

00:00:54.134 --> 00:00:56.672
Works from any OS — the only

00:00:56.672 --> 00:00:58.121
requirement is a browser.

00:00:58.647 --> 00:00:59.824
And there it is:

00:00:59.824 --> 00:01:00.412
VS Code,

00:01:00.412 --> 00:01:01.589
in a browser tab.

00:01:01.589 --> 00:01:04.236
The file tree on the left shows the repo,

00:01:04.236 --> 00:01:05.413
and only the repo.

00:01:11.147 --> 00:01:12.885
Let's create a real file,

00:01:12.885 --> 00:01:13.928
no terminal involved.

00:01:13.928 --> 00:01:14.970
A new editor,

00:01:14.970 --> 00:01:16.361
a couple of lines,

00:01:16.361 --> 00:01:19.141
and save it as notes slash todo dot

00:01:19.141 --> 00:01:19.489
md.

00:01:19.489 --> 00:01:22.269
The folder appears on the left as it

00:01:22.269 --> 00:01:23.660
lands in the repo.

00:01:29.647 --> 00:01:31.732
The built-in terminal works too,

00:01:31.732 --> 00:01:33.400
and there's our file.

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:35.901
Now let's try to look outside

00:01:35.901 --> 00:01:36.735
the repo:

00:01:36.735 --> 00:01:37.569
permission denied.

00:01:37.569 --> 00:01:39.237
That's not a setting,

00:01:39.237 --> 00:01:40.488
that's the kernel.

00:01:48.647 --> 00:01:50.685
Same repo from the plain terminal:

00:01:50.685 --> 00:01:52.722
the working directory is the repo,

00:01:52.722 --> 00:01:54.760
the files are the repo's files.

00:01:57.563 --> 00:02:00.087
Terminal and editor agree — it

00:02:00.087 --> 00:02:01.769
is the same sandbox.

00:02:05.033 --> 00:02:07.602
And the file we created in the

00:02:07.602 --> 00:02:08.336
browser editor?

00:02:08.336 --> 00:02:09.070
Right here.

00:02:09.070 --> 00:02:11.638
Files made in VS Code are real

00:02:11.638 --> 00:02:12.372
repo files,

00:02:12.372 --> 00:02:12.739
instantly.

00:02:14.489 --> 00:02:16.074
Created in the browser,

00:02:16.074 --> 00:02:17.659
readable from the terminal.

00:02:17.659 --> 00:02:18.451
One repo,

00:02:18.451 --> 00:02:19.243
two doors.

00:02:22.576 --> 00:02:24.184
Now try to leave.

00:02:24.184 --> 00:02:26.595
Listing the root of the server:

00:02:26.595 --> 00:02:27.399
permission denied.

00:02:27.399 --> 00:02:29.408
The kernel scopes the editor,

00:02:29.408 --> 00:02:30.212
its terminal,

00:02:30.212 --> 00:02:33.025
and every child process to this repo.

00:02:34.775 --> 00:02:36.715
Denied by the kernel,

00:02:36.715 --> 00:02:38.171
not by configuration.

00:02:41.482 --> 00:02:42.949
Other users' homes?

00:02:42.949 --> 00:02:43.926
Also denied.

00:02:43.926 --> 00:02:46.859
Whatever runs inside this sandbox —

00:02:46.859 --> 00:02:47.348
editors,

00:02:47.348 --> 00:02:47.837
terminals,

00:02:47.837 --> 00:02:50.770
build tools — ends at the

00:02:50.770 --> 00:02:51.748
repo's walls.

00:02:53.498 --> 00:02:55.385
The sandbox has no exceptions.

00:02:55.385 --> 00:02:56.894
That is the point.

00:02:57.688 --> 00:02:58.146
Browser,

00:02:58.146 --> 00:02:58.603
editor,

00:02:58.603 --> 00:02:59.061
terminal:

00:02:59.061 --> 00:02:59.977
same sandbox,

00:02:59.977 --> 00:03:00.892
same rules.

00:03:00.892 --> 00:03:03.638
Next up is the feature everything

00:03:03.638 --> 00:03:05.011
here builds on,

00:03:05.011 --> 00:03:05.469
forking.

00:03:05.469 --> 00:03:08.215
You're going to like this one.
